The paper deals with optimization problems in planar graphs, which are often studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The problems considered in the paper also involve packing and covering, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper presents approximation algorithms, which are often studied in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
